<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1678] JSON encoding of empty record should be &quot;{}&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1678</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An empty record (i.e. an instance of a record schema with no fields) should be encoded in JSON as &lt;tt&gt;&quot;{}&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;. (This is my interpretation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.7.7/spec.html#schema_record&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;the spec&lt;/a&gt;, which states only that records are encoded as JSON objects.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However as of Avro 1.7.7, the Java implementation yields &lt;tt&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;. This is the case for both generic and specific datum writers. Here is a failing test case (using generic):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Test
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testThis() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; Exception {
    Schema emptyRecordSchema = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Schema.Parser().parse(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;{\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;type\&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;:\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;record\&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;,\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;name\&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;:\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;EmptyRecord\&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;,\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;fields\&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;:[]}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    Schema arraySchema = Schema.createArray(emptyRecordSchema);

    GenericRecord emptyRecord = (GenericRecord) GenericData.get().newRecord(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;, emptyRecordSchema);
    GenericArray&amp;lt;GenericRecord&amp;gt; emptyArray = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GenericData.Array&amp;lt;&amp;gt;(arraySchema, Collections.&amp;lt;GenericRecord&amp;gt;emptyList());
    GenericArray&amp;lt;GenericRecord&amp;gt; arrayContainingEmptyRecord = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GenericData.Array&amp;lt;&amp;gt;(arraySchema, Arrays.asList(emptyRecord));

    Assert.assertThat(toJson(emptyArray), Matchers.is(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;[]&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// OK
&lt;/span&gt;    Assert.assertThat(toJson(arrayContainingEmptyRecord), Matchers.is(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;[{}]&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// OK
&lt;/span&gt;    Assert.assertThat(toJson(emptyRecord), Matchers.is(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;{}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fail: json is &quot;&quot;
&lt;/span&gt;}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; toJson(GenericContainer record) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    Schema schema = record.getSchema();
    ByteArrayOutputStream buffer = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ByteArrayOutputStream();
    ParsingEncoder encoder = EncoderFactory.get().jsonEncoder(schema, buffer);
    @SuppressWarnings(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;unchecked&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) DatumWriter&amp;lt;GenericContainer&amp;gt; writer = GenericData.get().createDatumWriter(schema);
    writer.write(record, encoder);
    encoder.flush();
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;(buffer.toByteArray(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
